# General Rules

## Communication

- Explain reasoning when making architectural decisions

## Tech Stack

- React + TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- React Router for navigation
- Vite as build tool

## TypeScript

- Always use explicit type annotations on every variable, parameter, and return type
- Never use `any` type — ever
- Use `type` over `interface`
- Use `unknown` for truly unknown types, then narrow with type guards
- Use `.prettierrc` file for formatting rule

## Code Style

- Use arrow functions over function declarations
- Always use `const` unless reassignment is necessary
- Destructure props and objects wherever possible
- No commented-out code
- No magic numbers — use named constants

## Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (UserCard.tsx)
- Functions/variables: camelCase (fetchUser)
- Types: PascalCase (UserCardProps)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_RETRY_COUNT)
- Files: kebab-case except components (user-list.ts / UserList.tsx)
- Abbreviations as whole words: loadHttpUrl not loadHTTPURL
- Event handlers:
  - props: onDelete, onClick, onChange
  - implementations: handleDelete, handleClick, handleChange

## File & Folder Structure

- pages/       → route-level components
- components/  → reusable UI components
- hooks/       → custom hooks
- api/         → API call functions
- types/       → shared type definitions
- lib/         → utility functions

## Google TypeScript Style Guide

- Never use `enum` — use `const` object with `as const` instead
  - ❌ enum Direction { Up = "up", Down = "down" }
  - ✅ const DIRECTION = { UP: "up", DOWN: "down" } as const
       type Direction = typeof DIRECTION[keyof typeof DIRECTION]
- Use optional chaining aggressively: user?.profile?.name
- Use nullish coalescing: value ?? defaultValue
- Prefer union types over function overloads
- Never use `namespace` — always use ES6 imports/exports
- Never use `obj['foo']` to bypass property visibility
- `export let` is not allowed — use explicit getter functions for mutable exports
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
  - ✅ import type { User } from "./types"
- Array type: use `Foo[]` over `Array<Foo>`
  - ✅ const users: `User[]`
  - ❌ const users: `Array<User>`
- Semicolons required at end of every statement
- Single quotes for strings (double quotes only in JSX attributes)
- 2 spaces for indentation — no tabs
- No trailing whitespace
- Blank lines at start or end of function body not allowed

## Google HTML/CSS Style Guide (applied to JSX + Tailwind)

- All HTML attributes lowercase
- Always include alt attributes on `<img>`
- Never use inline styles — keep structure and presentation separate
- Never use `!important` in CSS
- Avoid overly specific selectors — keep selector specificity low
- Semantic HTML over generic divs wherever possible
  - ✅ `<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`
  - ❌ `<div onClick={...}>` instead of `<button>`
- Always use HTTPS for external resources
